	<item>
		<title>Building for the Long Term</title>
		<link>https://acme-publishing.example/building-for-the-long-term/</link>
		<pubDate>Thu, 15 Jan 2026 08:30:00 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[jane]]></dc:creator>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Software outlives its authors when it is <strong>boring on purpose</strong>. This is our operating thesis.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2>What we optimize for</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li>Readability over cleverness</li><li>Deletion over addition</li><li>Standards over frameworks</li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":100,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"none"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img src="https://acme-publishing.example/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/hero-1024x683.jpg" alt="Team at the whiteboard" class="wp-image-100"/></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:quote -->
<blockquote class="wp-block-quote"><p>Durability is a feature.</p></blockquote>
<!-- /wp:quote -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>We wrote about our stack in <a href="https://acme-publishing.example/hello-cloudflare/">Hello Cloudflare</a>.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->]]></content:encoded>
		<excerpt:encoded><![CDATA[Why we build for decades, not quarters.]]></excerpt:encoded>
